Description: Fragment of flattened, tapering, handle, from neck join to sharp turn, of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '460'. Ink '1323,5' (an IG XII 1 number erroneously allocated, probably sent to IG as being from Rhodes?). Name Ippokrates.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (166)
